history.content:
Dear LS CS-intended Students,

 

In response to your questions regarding space in EE16A for Spring 2016, we plan to process enrollment in the following way:

 

  1.        EECS majors (all grades)
  2.        LSCS seniors and juniors (by Non-AP level)
  3.        COE majors: ME, Nuclear, BioEng, and Eng Undeclared (all grades)
  4.        Other majors (all grades)

 

There are ~100 seats which are available for any student on a first-come, first-served basis which could include more LSCS juniors as well as sophomores or currently undeclared intended LSCS majors.   Since those seats are limited, we suggest that any L&S student, other than declared LSCS 4th year seniors, who wishes to take 16A prioritize using Phase I of Telebears to enroll or waitlist for 16A if you want to have a chance to take the class in Spring 2016.

 

Sincerely,

EECS Center for Student Affairs Staff
